rComments: Liz grades with a Berkeley mind at a UCSC school.  Nice personality and charming lady, but her grading fairness was questionable.  I followed her suggestions perfectly for my second paper and then got graded down to a c+ because she disagreed with my conclusion.  Figure out what SHE thinks and then feed it to her and you will be golden.

Liz took over this class while Nancy Chen is on leave. She is a doctoral candidate in the medical anthro program at Berkeley.  As such, her handling of the class was a little shakey, but she fed us a lot of good information and thus covered the subject thoroughly.  My only complaint was the grading, 80% of which came in the final two weeks of class
